There is a way to modify objects. This uses the original syntax of incrementally adding properties but the parameter based initialization was more concise. Once an object is created the properties can be modified via attributes.
```
>>> from troposphere import Template
>>> from troposphere import s3
>>> t = Template()
>>> b = s3.Bucket("bucket")
>>> t.add_resource(b)
<troposphere.s3.Bucket object at 0x10372c1d0>
>>> print t.to_json()
{
    "Resources": {
        "bucket": {
            "Type": "AWS::S3::Bucket"
        }
    }
}
>>> b.BucketName = "mybucket"
>>> print t.to_json()
{
    "Resources": {
        "bucket": {
            "Properties": {
                "BucketName": "mybucket"
            },
            "Type": "AWS::S3::Bucket"
        }
    }
}
>>> b.BucketName = b.BucketName + "foobar"
>>> print t.to_json()
{
    "Resources": {
        "bucket": {
            "Properties": {
                "BucketName": "mybucketfoobar"
            },
            "Type": "AWS::S3::Bucket"
        }
    }
}
```

